{
  "texts": [
    "In regression, labels can be any real number Y = R. This is the case when we try to predict a numerical quantity such as CO 2 emissions, temperature, etc.",
    "A predictor is a function f: X → Y: for each object x, it returns a label f (x).",
    "We are usually interested in parametric sets of predictors.",
    "That is, we consider {f θ, θ ∈ Θ} where Θ is any set, called the parameter set, and each f θ is a predictor.",
    "For example, in linear regression, a common set of predictors is f θ (x) = ⟨x, θ⟩ ∈ Y = R, with X = Θ = R d."
  ]
}